80 // Weights are for internal use only. They are used by heuristics to help to ----
81 // estimate edges' probability. Example: ----
82 // ----
83 // Using "Loop Branch Heuristics" we predict weights of edges for the ----
84 // block BB2. ----
85 // ... ----
86 // | ----
87 // V ----
88 // BB1<-+ ----
89 // | | ----
90 // | | (Weight = 124) ----
91 // V | ----
92 // BB2--+ ----
93 // | ----
94 // | (Weight = 4) ----
95 // V ----
96 // BB3 ----
97 // ----
98 // Probability of the edge BB2->BB1 = 124 / (124 + 4) = 0.96875 ----
99 // Probability of the edge BB2->BB3 = 4 / (124 + 4) = 0.03125 ----
100 static const uint32_t LBH_TAKEN_WEIGHT = 124; ----
101 static const uint32_t LBH_NONTAKEN_WEIGHT = 4; ----

103 /// Unreachable-terminating branch taken probability. ----
104 /// ----
105 /// This is the probability for a branch being taken to a block that terminates ----
106 /// (eventually) in unreachable. These are predicted as unlikely as possible. ----
107 /// All reachable probability will proportionally share the remaining part. ----
108 static const BranchProbability UR_TAKEN_PROB = BranchProbability::getRaw(1); ----

158 /// strcmp and similar functions return zero, negative, or positive, if the ----
159 /// first string is equal, less, or greater than the second. We consider it ----
160 /// likely that the strings are not equal, so a comparison with zero is ----
161 /// probably false, but also a comparison with any other number is also ----
162 /// probably false given that what exactly is returned for nonzero values is ----
163 /// not specified. Any kind of comparison other than equality we know ----
164 /// nothing about. ----

196 /// Set of dedicated "absolute" execution weights for a block. These weights are ----
197 /// meaningful relative to each other and their derivatives only. ----
198 enum class BlockExecWeight : std::uint32_t { ----
199 /// Special weight used for cases with exact zero probability. ----
200 ZERO = 0x0, ----
201 /// Minimal possible non zero weight. ----
202 LOWEST_NON_ZERO = 0x1, ----
203 /// Weight to an 'unreachable' block. ----
204 UNREACHABLE = ZERO, ----
205 /// Weight to a block containing non returning call. ----
206 NORETURN = LOWEST_NON_ZERO, ----
207 /// Weight to 'unwind' block of an invoke instruction. ----
208 UNWIND = LOWEST_NON_ZERO, ----
209 /// Weight to a 'cold' block. Cold blocks are the ones containing calls marked ----
210 /// with attribute 'cold'. ----
211 COLD = 0xffff, ----
212 /// Default weight is used in cases when there is no dedicated execution ----
213 /// weight set. It is not propagated through the domination line either. ----
214 DEFAULT = 0xfffff ----
215 }; ----

375 // Propagate existing explicit probabilities from either profile data or ----
376 // 'expect' intrinsic processing. Examine metadata against unreachable ----
377 // heuristic. The probability of the edge coming to unreachable block is ----
378 // set to min of metadata and unreachable heuristic. ----
379 bool BranchProbabilityInfo::calcMetadataWeights(const BasicBlock *BB) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
380 const Instruction *TI = BB->getTerminator(); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
381 assert(TI->getNumSuccessors() > 1 && "expected more than one successor!"); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
382 if (!(isa(TI) || isa(TI) || isa(TI) || 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
383 isa(TI) || isa(TI))) 0
384 return false; 0
385 ----
386 MDNode *WeightsNode = getValidBranchWeightMDNode(*TI); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
387 if (!WeightsNode) 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
388 return false; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
389 ----
390 // Check that the number of successors is manageable. ----
391 assert(TI->getNumSuccessors() < UINT32_MAX && "Too many successors"); 0
392 ----
393 // Build up the final weights that will be used in a temporary buffer. ----
394 // Compute the sum of all weights to later decide whether they need to ----
395 // be scaled to fit in 32 bits. ----
396 uint64_t WeightSum = 0; 0
397 SmallVector Weights; 0
398 SmallVector UnreachableIdxs; 0
399 SmallVector ReachableIdxs; 0
400 ----
401 extractBranchWeights(WeightsNode, Weights); 0
402 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Weights.size(); I != E; ++I) { 0
403 WeightSum += Weights[I]; 0
404 const LoopBlock SrcLoopBB = getLoopBlock(BB); 0
405 const LoopBlock DstLoopBB = getLoopBlock(TI->getSuccessor(I)); 0
406 auto EstimatedWeight = getEstimatedEdgeWeight({SrcLoopBB, DstLoopBB}); 0
407 if (EstimatedWeight && 0
408 *EstimatedWeight <= static_cast(BlockExecWeight::UNREACHABLE)) 0
409 UnreachableIdxs.push_back(I); 0
410 else ----
411 ReachableIdxs.push_back(I); 0
412 } ----
413 assert(Weights.size() == TI->getNumSuccessors() && "Checked above"); 0
414 ----
415 // If the sum of weights does not fit in 32 bits, scale every weight down ----
416 // accordingly. ----
417 uint64_t ScalingFactor = 0
418 (WeightSum > UINT32_MAX) ? WeightSum / UINT32_MAX + 1 : 1; 0
419 ----
420 if (ScalingFactor > 1) { 0
421 WeightSum = 0; 0
422 for (unsigned I = 0, E = TI->getNumSuccessors(); I != E; ++I) { 0
423 Weights[I] /= ScalingFactor; 0
424 WeightSum += Weights[I]; 0
425 } ----
426 } ----
427 assert(WeightSum <= UINT32_MAX && 0
428 "Expected weights to scale down to 32 bits"); ----
429 ----
430 if (WeightSum == 0 || ReachableIdxs.size() == 0) { 0
431 for (unsigned I = 0, E = TI->getNumSuccessors(); I != E; ++I) 0
432 Weights[I] = 1; 0
433 WeightSum = TI->getNumSuccessors(); 0
434 } ----
435 ----
436 // Set the probability. ----
437 SmallVector BP; 0
438 for (unsigned I = 0, E = TI->getNumSuccessors(); I != E; ++I) 0
439 BP.push_back({ Weights[I], static_cast(WeightSum) }); 0
440 ----
441 // Examine the metadata against unreachable heuristic. ----
442 // If the unreachable heuristic is more strong then we use it for this edge. ----
443 if (UnreachableIdxs.size() == 0 || ReachableIdxs.size() == 0) { 0
444 setEdgeProbability(BB, BP); 0
445 return true; 0
446 } ----
447 ----
448 auto UnreachableProb = UR_TAKEN_PROB; 0
449 for (auto I : UnreachableIdxs) 0
450 if (UnreachableProb < BP[I]) { 0
451 BP[I] = UnreachableProb; 0
452 } ----
453 ----
454 // Sum of all edge probabilities must be 1.0. If we modified the probability ----
455 // of some edges then we must distribute the introduced difference over the ----
456 // reachable blocks. ----
457 // ----
458 // Proportional distribution: the relation between probabilities of the ----
459 // reachable edges is kept unchanged. That is for any reachable edges i and j: ----
460 // newBP[i] / newBP[j] == oldBP[i] / oldBP[j] => ----
461 // newBP[i] / oldBP[i] == newBP[j] / oldBP[j] == K ----
462 // Where K is independent of i,j. ----
463 // newBP[i] == oldBP[i] * K ----
464 // We need to find K. ----
465 // Make sum of all reachables of the left and right parts: ----
466 // sum_of_reachable(newBP) == K * sum_of_reachable(oldBP) ----
467 // Sum of newBP must be equal to 1.0: ----
468 // sum_of_reachable(newBP) + sum_of_unreachable(newBP) == 1.0 => ----
469 // sum_of_reachable(newBP) = 1.0 - sum_of_unreachable(newBP) ----
470 // Where sum_of_unreachable(newBP) is what has been just changed. ----
471 // Finally: ----
472 // K == sum_of_reachable(newBP) / sum_of_reachable(oldBP) => ----
473 // K == (1.0 - sum_of_unreachable(newBP)) / sum_of_reachable(oldBP) ----
474 BranchProbability NewUnreachableSum = BranchProbability::getZero(); 0
475 for (auto I : UnreachableIdxs) 0
476 NewUnreachableSum += BP[I]; 0
477 ----
478 BranchProbability NewReachableSum = ----
479 BranchProbability::getOne() - NewUnreachableSum; 0
480 ----
481 BranchProbability OldReachableSum = BranchProbability::getZero(); 0
482 for (auto I : ReachableIdxs) 0
483 OldReachableSum += BP[I]; 0
484 ----
485 if (OldReachableSum != NewReachableSum) { // Anything to dsitribute? 0
486 if (OldReachableSum.isZero()) { 0
487 // If all oldBP[i] are zeroes then the proportional distribution results ----
488 // in all zero probabilities and the error stays big. In this case we ----
489 // evenly spread NewReachableSum over the reachable edges. ----
490 BranchProbability PerEdge = NewReachableSum / ReachableIdxs.size(); 0
491 for (auto I : ReachableIdxs) 0
492 BP[I] = PerEdge; 0
493 } else { ----
494 for (auto I : ReachableIdxs) { 0
495 // We use uint64_t to avoid double rounding error of the following ----
496 // calculation: BP[i] = BP[i] * NewReachableSum / OldReachableSum ----
497 // The formula is taken from the private constructor ----
498 // BranchProbability(uint32_t Numerator, uint32_t Denominator) ----
499 uint64_t Mul = static_cast(NewReachableSum.getNumerator()) * 0
500 BP[I].getNumerator(); 0
501 uint32_t Div = static_cast( ----
502 divideNearest(Mul, OldReachableSum.getNumerator())); 0
503 BP[I] = BranchProbability::getRaw(Div); 0
504 } ----
505 } ----
506 } ----
507 ----
508 setEdgeProbability(BB, BP); 0
509 ----
510 return true; 0
511 } 0

514 // between two pointer or pointer and NULL will fail. ----
515 bool BranchProbabilityInfo::calcPointerHeuristics(const BasicBlock *BB) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
516 const BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast(BB->getTerminator()); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
517 if (!BI || !BI->isConditional()) 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
518 return false; 0
519 ----
520 Value *Cond = BI->getCondition(); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
521 ICmpInst *CI = dyn_cast(Cond); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
522 if (!CI || !CI->isEquality()) 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
523 return false; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
524 ----
525 Value *LHS = CI->getOperand(0); 0
526 ----
527 if (!LHS->getType()->isPointerTy()) 0
528 return false; 0
529 ----
530 assert(CI->getOperand(1)->getType()->isPointerTy()); 0
531 ----
532 auto Search = PointerTable.find(CI->getPredicate()); 0

539 // Compute the unlikely successors to the block BB in the loop L, specifically ----
540 // those that are unlikely because this is a loop, and add them to the ----
541 // UnlikelyBlocks set. ----
542 static void ----
543 computeUnlikelySuccessors(const BasicBlock *BB, Loop *L, 0
544 SmallPtrSetImpl &UnlikelyBlocks) { ----
545 // Sometimes in a loop we have a branch whose condition is made false by ----
546 // taking it. This is typically something like ----
547 // int n = 0; ----
548 // while (...) { ----
549 // if (++n >= MAX) { ----
550 // n = 0; ----
551 // } ----
552 // } ----
553 // In this sort of situation taking the branch means that at the very least it ----
554 // won't be taken again in the next iteration of the loop, so we should ----
555 // consider it less likely than a typical branch. ----
556 // ----
557 // We detect this by looking back through the graph of PHI nodes that sets the ----
558 // value that the condition depends on, and seeing if we can reach a successor ----
559 // block which can be determined to make the condition false. ----
560 // ----
561 // FIXME: We currently consider unlikely blocks to be half as likely as other ----
562 // blocks, but if we consider the example above the likelyhood is actually ----
563 // 1/MAX. We could therefore be more precise in how unlikely we consider ----
564 // blocks to be, but it would require more careful examination of the form ----
565 // of the comparison expression. ----
566 const BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast(BB->getTerminator()); 0
567 if (!BI || !BI->isConditional()) 0
568 return; 0
569 ----
570 // Check if the branch is based on an instruction compared with a constant ----
571 CmpInst *CI = dyn_cast(BI->getCondition()); 0
572 if (!CI || !isa(CI->getOperand(0)) || 0
573 !isa(CI->getOperand(1))) 0
574 return; 0
575 ----
576 // Either the instruction must be a PHI, or a chain of operations involving ----
577 // constants that ends in a PHI which we can then collapse into a single value ----
578 // if the PHI value is known. ----
579 Instruction *CmpLHS = dyn_cast(CI->getOperand(0)); 0
580 PHINode *CmpPHI = dyn_cast(CmpLHS); 0
581 Constant *CmpConst = dyn_cast(CI->getOperand(1)); 0
582 // Collect the instructions until we hit a PHI ----
583 SmallVector InstChain; 0
584 while (!CmpPHI && CmpLHS && isa(CmpLHS) && 0
585 isa(CmpLHS->getOperand(1))) { 0
586 // Stop if the chain extends outside of the loop ----
587 if (!L->contains(CmpLHS)) 0
588 return; 0
589 InstChain.push_back(cast(CmpLHS)); 0
590 CmpLHS = dyn_cast(CmpLHS->getOperand(0)); 0
591 if (CmpLHS) 0
592 CmpPHI = dyn_cast(CmpLHS); 0
593 } ----
594 if (!CmpPHI || !L->contains(CmpPHI)) 0
595 return; 0
596 ----
597 // Trace the phi node to find all values that come from successors of BB ----
598 SmallPtrSet VisitedInsts; 0
599 SmallVector WorkList; 0
600 WorkList.push_back(CmpPHI); 0
601 VisitedInsts.insert(CmpPHI); 0
602 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
603 PHINode *P = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
604 for (BasicBlock *B : P->blocks()) { 0
605 // Skip blocks that aren't part of the loop ----
606 if (!L->contains(B)) 0
607 continue; 0
608 Value *V = P->getIncomingValueForBlock(B); 0
609 // If the source is a PHI add it to the work list if we haven't ----
610 // already visited it. ----
611 if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
612 if (VisitedInsts.insert(PN).second) 0
613 WorkList.push_back(PN); 0
614 continue; 0
615 } ----
616 // If this incoming value is a constant and B is a successor of BB, then ----
617 // we can constant-evaluate the compare to see if it makes the branch be ----
618 // taken or not. ----
619 Constant *CmpLHSConst = dyn_cast(V); 0
620 if (!CmpLHSConst || !llvm::is_contained(successors(BB), B)) 0
621 continue; 0
622 // First collapse InstChain ----
623 const DataLayout &DL = BB->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
624 for (Instruction *I : llvm::reverse(InstChain)) { 0
625 CmpLHSConst = ConstantFoldBinaryOpOperands( 0
626 I->getOpcode(), CmpLHSConst, cast(I->getOperand(1)), DL); ----
627 if (!CmpLHSConst) 0
628 break; 0
629 } ----
630 if (!CmpLHSConst) 0
631 continue; 0
632 // Now constant-evaluate the compare ----
633 Constant *Result = ConstantExpr::getCompare(CI->getPredicate(), 0
634 CmpLHSConst, CmpConst, true); ----
635 // If the result means we don't branch to the block then that block is ----
636 // unlikely. ----
637 if (Result && 0
638 ((Result->isZeroValue() && B == BI->getSuccessor(0)) || 0
639 (Result->isOneValue() && B == BI->getSuccessor(1)))) 0
640 UnlikelyBlocks.insert(B); 0
641 } ----
642 } ----
643 } 0

650 return WeightIt->second; 0

670 template ----
671 std::optional BranchProbabilityInfo::getMaxEstimatedEdgeWeight( 0
672 const LoopBlock &SrcLoopBB, iterator_range Successors) const { ----
673 SmallVector Weights; 0
674 std::optional MaxWeight; 0
675 for (const BasicBlock *DstBB : Successors) { 0
676 const LoopBlock DstLoopBB = getLoopBlock(DstBB); 0
677 auto Weight = getEstimatedEdgeWeight({SrcLoopBB, DstLoopBB}); 0
678 ----
679 if (!Weight) 0
680 return std::nullopt; 0
681 ----
682 if (!MaxWeight || *MaxWeight < *Weight) 0
683 MaxWeight = Weight; 0
684 } ----
685 ----
686 return MaxWeight; 0
687 } 0
688 ----
689 // Updates \p LoopBB's weight and returns true. If \p LoopBB has already ----
690 // an associated weight it is unchanged and false is returned. ----
691 // ----
692 // Please note by the algorithm the weight is not expected to change once set ----
693 // thus 'false' status is used to track visited blocks. ----
694 bool BranchProbabilityInfo::updateEstimatedBlockWeight( 0
695 LoopBlock &LoopBB, uint32_t BBWeight, ----
696 SmallVectorImpl &BlockWorkList, ----
697 SmallVectorImpl &LoopWorkList) { ----
698 BasicBlock *BB = LoopBB.getBlock(); 0
699 ----
700 // In general, weight is assigned to a block when it has final value and ----
701 // can't/shouldn't be changed. However, there are cases when a block ----
702 // inherently has several (possibly "contradicting") weights. For example, ----
703 // "unwind" block may also contain "cold" call. In that case the first ----
704 // set weight is favored and all consequent weights are ignored. ----
705 if (!EstimatedBlockWeight.insert({BB, BBWeight}).second) 0
706 return false; 0
707 ----
708 for (BasicBlock *PredBlock : predecessors(BB)) { 0
709 LoopBlock PredLoop = getLoopBlock(PredBlock); 0
710 // Add affected block/loop to a working list. ----
711 if (isLoopExitingEdge({PredLoop, LoopBB})) { 0
712 if (!EstimatedLoopWeight.count(PredLoop.getLoopData())) 0
713 LoopWorkList.push_back(PredLoop); 0
714 } else if (!EstimatedBlockWeight.count(PredBlock)) 0
715 BlockWorkList.push_back(PredBlock); 0
716 } ----
717 return true; 0
718 } ----
719 ----
720 // Starting from \p BB traverse through dominator blocks and assign \p BBWeight ----
721 // to all such blocks that are post dominated by \BB. In other words to all ----
722 // blocks that the one is executed if and only if another one is executed. ----
723 // Importantly, we skip loops here for two reasons. First weights of blocks in ----
724 // a loop should be scaled by trip count (yet possibly unknown). Second there is ----
725 // no any value in doing that because that doesn't give any additional ----
726 // information regarding distribution of probabilities inside the loop. ----
727 // Exception is loop 'enter' and 'exit' edges that are handled in a special way ----
728 // at calcEstimatedHeuristics. ----
729 // ----
730 // In addition, \p WorkList is populated with basic blocks if at leas one ----
731 // successor has updated estimated weight. ----
732 void BranchProbabilityInfo::propagateEstimatedBlockWeight( 0
733 const LoopBlock &LoopBB, DominatorTree *DT, PostDominatorTree *PDT, ----
734 uint32_t BBWeight, SmallVectorImpl &BlockWorkList, ----
735 SmallVectorImpl &LoopWorkList) { ----
736 const BasicBlock *BB = LoopBB.getBlock(); 0
737 const auto *DTStartNode = DT->getNode(BB); 0
738 const auto *PDTStartNode = PDT->getNode(BB); 0
739 ----
740 // TODO: Consider propagating weight down the domination line as well. ----
741 for (const auto *DTNode = DTStartNode; DTNode != nullptr; 0
742 DTNode = DTNode->getIDom()) { 0
743 auto *DomBB = DTNode->getBlock(); 0
744 // Consider blocks which lie on one 'line'. ----
745 if (!PDT->dominates(PDTStartNode, PDT->getNode(DomBB))) 0
746 // If BB doesn't post dominate DomBB it will not post dominate dominators ----
747 // of DomBB as well. ----
748 break; 0
749 ----
750 LoopBlock DomLoopBB = getLoopBlock(DomBB); 0
751 const LoopEdge Edge{DomLoopBB, LoopBB}; 0
752 // Don't propagate weight to blocks belonging to different loops. ----
753 if (!isLoopEnteringExitingEdge(Edge)) { 0
754 if (!updateEstimatedBlockWeight(DomLoopBB, BBWeight, BlockWorkList, 0
755 LoopWorkList)) ----
756 // If DomBB has weight set then all it's predecessors are already ----
757 // processed (since we propagate weight up to the top of IR each time). ----
758 break; 0
759 } else if (isLoopExitingEdge(Edge)) { 0
760 LoopWorkList.push_back(DomLoopBB); 0
761 } ----
762 } ----
763 } 0

1131 /// Set the edge probability for all edges at once. ----
1132 void BranchProbabilityInfo::setEdgeProbability( 0
1133 const BasicBlock *Src, const SmallVectorImpl &Probs) { ----
1134 assert(Src->getTerminator()->getNumSuccessors() == Probs.size()); 0
1135 eraseBlock(Src); // Erase stale data if any. 0
1136 if (Probs.size() == 0) 0
1137 return; // Nothing to set. 0
1138 ----
1139 Handles.insert(BasicBlockCallbackVH(Src, this)); 0
1140 uint64_t TotalNumerator = 0; 0
1141 for (unsigned SuccIdx = 0; SuccIdx < Probs.size(); ++SuccIdx) { 0
1142 this->Probs[std::make_pair(Src, SuccIdx)] = Probs[SuccIdx]; 0
1143 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "set edge " << Src->getName() << " -> " << SuccIdx 0
1144 << " successor probability to " << Probs[SuccIdx] ----
1145 << "\n"); ----
1146 TotalNumerator += Probs[SuccIdx].getNumerator(); 0
1147 } ----
1148 ----
1149 // Because of rounding errors the total probability cannot be checked to be ----
1150 // 1.0 exactly. That is TotalNumerator == BranchProbability::getDenominator. ----
1151 // Instead, every single probability in Probs must be as accurate as possible. ----
1152 // This results in error 1/denominator at most, thus the total absolute error ----
1153 // should be within Probs.size / BranchProbability::getDenominator. ----
1154 assert(TotalNumerator <= BranchProbability::getDenominator() + Probs.size()); 0
1155 assert(TotalNumerator >= BranchProbability::getDenominator() - Probs.size()); 0
1156 (void)TotalNumerator; ----
1157 } ----

1200 ----
1201 // Note that we cannot use successors of BB because the terminator of BB may ----

1207 // setEdgeProbability(). ----

1212 assert(Probs.count(std::make_pair(BB, I + 1)) == 0 && 0
1213 "Must be no more successors"); ----
1214 return; 0
1215 } ----
